Sampati (सम्पति), yet another new Nepali Lok Dohori song by Shrota Sangeet, is a pure love song written by Pralhad Subedi and brought into life by two of the most prominent Lok singers: Kushal Belbase and Sunita Budha Chhetri, following the musical progression of Basanta Thapa.

Shrota Sangeet Pvt. Ltd. presents a new Nepali Lok Dohori Song: Sampati सम्पति by Kushal Belbase, Sunita Budha, Niks Sharma, and Gita Dhungana.

𝑷𝒓𝒂𝒍𝒉𝒂𝒅 𝑺𝒖𝒃𝒆𝒅𝒊, the thought-provoking lyricist has portrayed perfectly that, every relationship is a blessed property.

The refrain roughly translates to "Please don't ask for my gain. You're the one with whom my life is blessed”. In other words, if you ever ask, what I have accumulated in life, you are the answer. 

In a nutshell, the song Sampati (सम्पति) might trigger right the people in their mid-30s esp. in Nepali society.

For more to relate, please enjoy watching the full video by an amazing team led by 𝐌𝐚𝐮𝐬𝐚𝐦 𝐇𝐢𝐦𝐚𝐥𝐢, one of the established names in the industry, cast by Niks Sharma, Gita Dhungana, and Prakash Ghimire. The video was filmed in Pumdi village on the outskirts of Pokhara.
